PIO
A high-level Parallel I/O Library for structured grid applications

PIO is an intermediate software layer the allows you to write data in 
either binary or netcdf format using either serial writes or parallel 
libraries such as MPI-IO and PnetCDF through a single interface.

We have a mailing list through Google Groups.

PIO is written in Fortran90.

NEW inline documentation with doxygen 
http://web.ncar.teragrid.org/~dennis/pio_doc/html/

Source Code Available

Obtain the source code by svn checkout: 
svn co http://parallelio.googlecode.com/svn/trunk 
